No fewer than 10 pastors have been arrested in Eket, Akwa Ibom State by the task force on the restriction of movement and social gathering by the state government. Last week, Governor Udom Emmanuel announced the prohibition of religious and social gatherings to curb the spread of the coronavirus epidemic. However, in defiance to the government’s directive, some churches in Eket, held their normal Sunday services. LEADERSHIP gathered that the Eket branch pastor or the Deeper Life Bible Church and a pastor of the United African Evangelical Church were among those arrested by the police. Our correspondent who was at the Eket Police Divisional headquarters, saw the detainees where they sat on a long bench with their bibles. The divisional police officer (DPO), Mr Sunday Diggah, said that the pastors might be prosecuted for violating the state government’s stay-at-home order.